                    <span>A good book does not need to be complex. This one does a great job. You could read this book during one hour and learn more than in one semester of COS111. It is so simple. Comcepts are the most important thing to learn. They give meaning to programing. Without concepts, programing becomes meaningless.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">As clear as it gets!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
